Adeniyi Olugbemi, Sokoto SOKOTO State Government and foreign donor agencies of Qatar Charity and Future Leaders from Arab nations on Tuesday laid foundation for the building of a new city of 150 houses for IDP’s situated in Gandi town of Rabah Local Government Area of the state. Flagging off the foundation laying of the first cluster of 50 houses, Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal, represented by the Deputy Governor, Manir Dan’iya, lauded the kind gesture of Arab organisations for coming to the aid of Gandi IDPs. Tambuwal said, “The state government made all arrangements to compensate the land owners, where the houses will be built in Gandi town. Therefore, all relevant agencies should work round the clock for the speedy completion of the project and be put to use.” Also, the Sultan of Sokoto, Sa’ad Abubakar, thanked the organisations for coming to the aid of Gandi IDPs with a magnificent modern city as a permanent settlement away from their places ravaged by bandits and insecurity. In their remarks, Shiek Elshami Noshiali Elshami, who spoke on behalf of Qatar Charity and Future Leaders, said the charity organisations agreed to seek Sokoto State Government’s blessing under Zakkat and Waqf Commission to help Muslim brothers in need at their trying times. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 